After cloning the capstone repo run:
git submodule update --init --recursive

To add other submodules to this github repo run:
git submodule add <repo-url> <folder-name>
cd <folder-name> && git remote set-url --push origin no_push
This is only for read-only repos. To be able to modify it we have to fork first then follow the setup below:

--- Linien submodule setup. Note: claude made this for me lol ---
The linien/ folder is a git submodule pointed at our team fork.

Remotes inside linien/:
origin -> https://github.com/Antily15503/linien (fetch + push, our fork)
upstream -> https://github.com/linien-org/linien (fetch only, push disabled)

To push your changes:
cd linien
git push origin <branch>

To pull upstream linien updates into our fork:
cd linien
git fetch upstream
git merge upstream/main
